=== Adjective ===
'''old''' ([[older]], [[oldest]]; [[elder]], [[eldest]])

#Something that has existed for a long period of time.
#Of a former time

====Synonyms====
*(''something that has existed''): [[ancient]] : very old
* (''of a former''): [[past]], [[tired]], [[worn]]

====Antonyms====
*(''something that has existed''): [[new]] (things), [[young]] (animals)
*(''of a former''): [[fresh]], [[newborn]]

====Example usage====
* (''of a former''): '''1994:''' “But over my '''old''' life, a new life had formed.”  -''Life Drawing'', Michael Grumley

